                                    </dd>
            
                            <dt>Title</dt>
                <dd>Small Is Beautiful, Less Is More</dd>
            
                                                                                                            
                            <dt>Classification</dt>
                <dd>Paintings</dd>
                                        <dt>Work Type</dt>
                <dd>
                                                            album folio,                                          painting                                                      </dd>
                                        <dt>Date</dt>
                <dd>1989</dd>
                                                                <dt>Culture</dt>
                <dd>Chinese</dd>
                            <dt>Persistent Link</dt>
                <dd><a href="https://hvrd.art/o/319292">https://hvrd.art/o/319292</a></dd>
          </dl>
        </dd>

        
                <dt>Physical Descriptions</dt>
        <dd>
          <dl>
                          <dt>Medium</dt>
              <dd>Accordion-fold album of twelve center-folded leaves, featuring the twelve symbols of the Chinese zodiac in sequential order; ink and ink and color on paper, with artist’s inscriptions</dd>
            
           
           
                          <dt>Dimensions</dt>
              <dd>each leaf: 16.8 x 23.8 cm (6 5/8 x 9 3/8 in.)<br />
closed album: 17 × 12 × 2.5 cm (6 11/16 × 4 3/4 × 1 in.)</dd>
            
            
            
            
            
                          <dt>Inscriptions and Marks</dt>
              <dd>
                                  <ul class="unstyled-list">
                                          <li data-a="1">
                        Signed: Title page, black ink: Written by Chen Qikuan, 1989 (Chinese brush-written characters followed by a red seal reading "Chen Qikuan yin")
                      </li>
                    
                                                                  <li data-a="2">
                          inscription: brush-written on opening page translates as follows: "On the elegant request of my elder brother, Chu-tsing, and his wife, Yaowen. Written by Chen Qikuan, 1989. Small is Beautiful, Less is More."
                        </li>
                                              <li data-a="2">
                          seal: artist's seal: Square red relief seal, following signature: "Chen Qikuan yin"
                        </li>
                                              <li data-a="2">
                          inscription: brush-written on twelve leaves: Leaf 1) "The jiazi year [1984]. Live Together in Peace. Spring Plum."<br />
Leaf 2) "The yichou year [1985]. Half-Day Break in the Fleeting Life. Chance Meeting."<br />
Leaf 3) "The bingyin year [1986]. Tiger-Shaped Talisman. In Spring, Flowers Fly Everywhere in the City."<br />
Leaf 4) "The dingmao year [1987]. Flying Leap. Roots."<br />
Leaf 5) "Riding the Dragon. The wuchen year [1988]. Drinking One's Fill."<br />
Leaf 6) "The jisi year [1989]. Deja Vu. Fresh."<br />
Leaf 7) "The gengwu year [1990]. Prairie. Autumn Colors."<br />
Leaf 8) "The xinwei year [1991]. Auspicious. Longevity. A Surplus."<br />
Leaf 9) "The renshen year [1992]. Home. Geese Flying South."<br />
Leaf 10) "The quiyou year [1993]. Opportunity. Pickled Vegetables."<br />
Leaf 11) "The jiaxu year [1994]. Team Spirit. Winter Scene."<br />
Leaf 12) "The yihai year [1995]. Lifeline."
                        </li>
                                          
                    
                                      </ul>
                              </dd>
            
          </dl>
        </dd>
        
                  <dt>Provenance</dt>
          <dd>Chen Qikuan, Burlingame, CA, 1989, gift; to Chu-tsing Li, Lawrence, Kansas (1989 -2012), gift; to his son B U.K. Li, Milwaukee, Wisconsin (2012-2016), gift; to Harvard Art Museums, 2016.<br />
<br />
Footnotes:<br />
